{
  "texts": [
    "SVM can perform both classification and regression tasks.",
    "It begins with labeled training data.",
    "Normalization or scaling of data is essential to ensure optimal results.",
    "During training, an SVM algorithm finds the optimal hyperplane or decision boundary to separate the data into different classes, calculated by finding support vectors and maximizing the margin (i.e., the distance between support vectors and the boundary).",
    "Mathematical optimization techniques are employed to optimize the margin while minimizing classification errors."
  ]
}